{"name":"Mathlib.Data.Polynomial.DenomsClearable","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Data.Polynomial.EraseLead","Mathlib.Data.Polynomial.Eval"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Data/Polynomial/DenomsClearable.lean#L94-L111","name":"one_le_pow_mul_abs_eval_div","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Polynomial/DenomsClearable.html#one_le_pow_mul_abs_eval_div","doc":"Evaluating a polynomial with integer coefficients at a rational number and clearing\ndenominators, yields a number greater than or equal to one.  The target can be any\n`LinearOrderedField K`.\nThe assumption on `K` could be weakened to `LinearOrderedCommRing` assuming that the\nimage of the denominator is invertible in `K`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Data/Polynomial/DenomsClearable.lean#L80-L82","name":"denomsClearable_natDegree","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Polynomial/DenomsClearable.html#denomsClearable_natDegree","doc":"If `i : R → K` is a ring homomorphism, `f` is a polynomial with coefficients in `R`,\n`a, b` are elements of `R`, with `i b` invertible, then there is a `D ∈ R` such that\n`b ^ f.natDegree * f (a / b)` equals `i D`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Data/Polynomial/DenomsClearable.lean#L71-L74","name":"denomsClearable_of_natDegree_le","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Polynomial/DenomsClearable.html#denomsClearable_of_natDegree_le","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Data/Polynomial/DenomsClearable.lean#L62-L68","name":"DenomsClearable.add","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Polynomial/DenomsClearable.html#DenomsClearable.add","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Data/Polynomial/DenomsClearable.lean#L51-L58","name":"denomsClearable_C_mul_X_pow","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Polynomial/DenomsClearable.html#denomsClearable_C_mul_X_pow","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Data/Polynomial/DenomsClearable.lean#L46-L48","name":"denomsClearable_zero","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Polynomial/DenomsClearable.html#denomsClearable_zero","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Data/Polynomial/DenomsClearable.lean#L42-L43","name":"DenomsClearable","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Polynomial/DenomsClearable.html#DenomsClearable","doc":"`denomsClearable` formalizes the property that `b ^ N * f (a / b)`\ndoes not have denominators, if the inequality `f.natDegree ≤ N` holds.\n\nThe definition asserts the existence of an element `D` of `R` and an\nelement `bi = 1 / i b` of `K` such that clearing the denominators of\nthe fraction equals `i D`.\n"}]}